The paper deals with face recognition using deep learning methods, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and conditional generative adversarial nets (cGANs). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves multi-modal matching and fusion of results, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of cGANs for depth image reconstruction could also place the paper in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves training and optimization of neural networks, which could fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
